From: NextOS Elite <noreply@nextos.local>
Subject: [PATCH] include/errno.h: delegate to system when HOSTCC

u-boot/include/errno.h declara 'extern int errno;' (não-TLS), mas glibc
moderno define errno como __thread (TLS). Linker rejeita: 'errno: TLS
definition in libc.so.6 does not match non-TLS reference'.

Fix: quando USE_HOSTCC, delega pro system errno.h via include_next.

---
 include/errno.h | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/include/errno.h b/include/errno.h
--- a/include/errno.h
+++ b/include/errno.h
@@ -1,5 +1,10 @@
 #ifndef _ERRNO_H
 
+#ifdef USE_HOSTCC
+/* Host tools: delega pro errno.h do sistema (errno TLS moderno). */
+#include_next <errno.h>
+#else
+
 #include <asm-generic/errno.h>
 
 extern int errno;
@@ -9,4 +14,5 @@
 #ifdef CONFIG_ERRNO_STR
 const char *errno_str(int errno);
 #endif
+#endif /* !USE_HOSTCC */
 #endif /* _ERRNO_H */
